Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the
spaghetti. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @spaghetti{180%g} and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a
#colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through
to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{}
on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and
shallot. Stir-fry until the bacon is cooked and the shallot has softened,
~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook
> lardons thoroughly.

In the meantime, roughly chop the @hazelnuts{25%g}.

Once the bacon is cooked and the shallot has softened, add the garlic and
stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water for the sauce{150%ml}.
Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g},
@peas{120%g} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss the cooked spaghetti
into the sauce and warm through until piping hot.

Stir in the @truffle zest{1%tsp}, then remove from the heat.

Share the truffled bacon and pea pasta between your #bowls{}.

Finish by sprinkling over the hazelnuts.

Enjoy!